= Luwrain Git repositories =

The~source code of~Luwrain can be easily accessed through   a~set of~Git repositories  hosted on~[[http://github.com/ github.com]].
All of~them listed here with the~short comments to~help you better understand their purpose.
Any~information about the~license for~these materials 
you can find on~[local:/doc/legal/ corresponding page with~legal notes].

== The main Luwrain repository ==

* [[http://github.com/luwrain/luwrain.git/ git://github.com/luwrain/luwrain.git]]

The~main Git repository contains  the~code 
of~the~environment core and the~code of~a~set of~standard applications.
This code is~supposed to~be completely system-independent,
meaning, it may not include any JNI references  or be linked with libraries available on~GNU/Linux only.

== Linux-dependent code ==

* [[http://github.com/luwrain/linux.git/ git://github.com/luwrain/linux.git]]

This repository contains JNI wrappers for~access to~Linux-specific functions 
(e.g.~for Linux terminal implementation).
It may be linked with any Linux-specific jar's
(e.g. for~interaction with~D-Bus).

== Luwrain extensions ==

* [[http://github.com/luwrain/extensions.git/ git://github.com/luwrain/extensions.git]]

The~extensions library for~Luwrain includes various add-ons 
not~chosen for~sustained support yet.
This~repository gets contributions from~everybody who is~willing to~enhance 
range of~supported services and technologies. 

== The~AT-SPI client and the~window manager ==

* [[http://github.com/luwrain/guidecraft.git/ git://github.com/luwrain/guidecraft.git]]

For~the~support of~some closed applications and for~work of~web-browsers Luwrain  includes the~AT-SPI client  
shipped with the~lightweight window manager for~easy control over a~set of~opened windows, including the~main window of~Luwrain itself.
This~utility called GuideCraft and in~contrast to~the~code of~Luwrain core and applications,
 is~written on~C++.

== The~D-Bus interface for~sending speech commands ==

* [[http://github.com/luwrain/libdbusspeech.git/ git://github.com/luwrain/libdbusspeech.git]]

This~repository contains C++ library which implements 
the~behaviour of~"proxy" object for~exchanging of~speech~commands.
This~library is~being prepared to~simplify implementation of~the~speech servers compatible with~Luwrain on~GNU/Linux. 

